WEBVTT

00:05.088 --> 00:06.214
Previously, on
"Below Deck Mediterranean"...

00:07.340 --> 00:08.341
This'll be a shorter charter...

00:08.383 --> 00:10.176
Anthony Evans and Chris Loar.

00:10.218 --> 00:12.178
Anthony is a gospel artist.

00:12.220 --> 00:14.514
They'd love to get off
the boat for a picnic.

00:14.556 --> 00:16.641
Man, I'm so grateful that they
took all this stuff up here.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.643
-My back.
-Like [bleep].

00:18.685 --> 00:22.480
Obviously, Lexi's been let go,
and we have two charters left.

00:26.568 --> 00:28.486
I do not want the client
to feel the impact.

00:28.528 --> 00:30.113
How are you guys gonna
do it with two people?

00:30.155 --> 00:31.406
Isn't that gonna be crazy?

00:33.324 --> 00:36.286
I work better under
physical pressure.

00:36.327 --> 00:37.787
I'm better at my job
when I'm running around

00:37.829 --> 00:39.205
like a headless chicken.

00:39.247 --> 00:41.207
Two-person team,
better than four.

00:41.249 --> 00:42.709
A lot of work for us, though.

00:42.751 --> 00:44.210
The dinner was excellent.

00:44.252 --> 00:46.379
My plate had a lot
of dark fish,

00:46.421 --> 00:48.298
so I don't think you
should ever serve that.

00:48.340 --> 00:52.218
I feel insecure when
I get any criticism.

00:52.260 --> 00:54.346
My last boat,
my captain would be,

00:54.387 --> 00:56.097
like, horrible words
the whole time.

00:57.599 --> 01:00.310
Leaving such a supportive
bubble, I'm concerned.

01:00.352 --> 01:02.395
Trying to get that level
of acceptance from new people.

01:04.230 --> 01:05.565
[gasps]
Dave!

01:05.607 --> 01:08.360
You should have come
to me that he was hurt!

01:08.401 --> 01:10.612
It's gonna be Mzi mornings,
Dave lates.

01:10.653 --> 01:12.405
Lloyd and Mzi
will now just kinda

01:12.447 --> 01:13.531
have to step up their game.

01:16.159 --> 01:18.370
There's a lot of responsibility
in the morning shift.

01:18.411 --> 01:20.080
I completely forgot
about the paddleboards.

01:20.121 --> 01:21.623
Please take
the anchor ball down.

01:21.664 --> 01:23.667
-Oh, sorry.
-For [bleep]'s sake.

01:23.708 --> 01:25.585
-What up?
-David, get out on deck.

01:25.627 --> 01:26.878
I think people are
getting tired.

01:26.920 --> 01:29.381
Six minutes till we
get to the marina.

01:29.422 --> 01:30.548
[bleep]'s sake.

01:30.590 --> 01:32.592
Five feet off the dock.

01:32.634 --> 01:33.760
Come on, Mzi.

01:33.802 --> 01:35.470
Ugh [bleep].

01:35.512 --> 01:37.764
Okay, we can put this one on,
we can put this one on.

01:37.806 --> 01:40.600
We're about to hit some
ground lines, and it's my fault.

01:40.642 --> 01:41.768
[bleep]'s sake.

01:59.577 --> 02:02.247
Getting stern lines across now.

02:02.288 --> 02:03.289
Come on, Mzi.

02:03.331 --> 02:06.501
-Ah.
-Quick.

02:06.543 --> 02:08.211
Ugh [bleep].

02:08.253 --> 02:10.505
Okay, we can put this one on,
we can put this one on.

02:10.547 --> 02:12.215
<i>Bump ahead.</i>

02:12.257 --> 02:14.342
The port dolphin is right
in front of me, I can't.

02:14.384 --> 02:15.635
Guys, we need to hurry.

02:15.677 --> 02:17.804
<i>Kick the stern</i>
<i>to port five feet.</i>

02:17.846 --> 02:20.306
-Mzi, where we at?
-Almost there.

02:20.348 --> 02:21.349
Okay, wait, we have to watch
them throw the rope.

02:23.476 --> 02:25.186
You don't have to throw it
where the line's going,

02:25.228 --> 02:26.563
you throw it the
shortest distance.

02:26.604 --> 02:29.357
-Cool.
-Let's throw, Mzi, come on.

02:29.399 --> 02:31.901
<i>Lloyd, Malia, talk to me...</i>
<i>what's going on on the bow?</i>

02:31.943 --> 02:34.404
Port bowline on, waiting for
my starboard line on.

02:34.446 --> 02:35.655
<i>-Hurry.</i>
-Sorry.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.532
What in God's name
did you do here?

02:37.574 --> 02:39.242
I'm kinda at my wits' end

02:39.284 --> 02:40.785
with how many mistakes
are being made.

02:40.827 --> 02:44.205
Mzi ----ed up that line,
and Lloyd...

02:44.247 --> 02:46.291
dude, you forgot
the anchor ball.

02:46.332 --> 02:48.418
Come on, we're making
----ing rookie mistakes.

02:48.460 --> 02:50.211
Just take up all the tension
by hand

02:50.253 --> 02:51.296
and lock it off on the cleat.

02:53.423 --> 02:55.592
Lloyd, which one are you
taking up tension first?

02:55.633 --> 02:57.302
Starboard, as we're
quite far over.

02:57.344 --> 02:58.511
<i>Copy, that works for us.</i>

02:58.553 --> 03:01.348
Drop-off day.
How did we do this?

03:08.730 --> 03:10.857
It would have been all right if
Delaney was here from the start.

03:10.899 --> 03:12.400
Yeah, that is true.

03:12.442 --> 03:13.568
Because then, like, she
would have been trained.

03:13.610 --> 03:15.528
Yeah.

03:15.570 --> 03:16.571
How's your laund looking?

03:16.613 --> 03:18.406
Looking good.

03:18.448 --> 03:19.699
Have you checked with Captain
Sandy, are her sheets done?

03:19.741 --> 03:20.825
-Yeah.
-Thanks, Coco.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.285
You're welcome.

03:25.538 --> 03:27.791
-Get ready.
-Okay.

03:31.795 --> 03:35.507
On the starboard line,
we are now at tension.

03:35.548 --> 03:36.633
Copy, understood.

03:36.675 --> 03:37.717
<i>Nice work.</i>

03:37.759 --> 03:38.885
[sighs]

03:39.886 --> 03:41.846
I still have to do the closet.

03:44.391 --> 03:45.767
-Oh, yeah, yeah.
-Yeah.

03:45.809 --> 03:46.810
Should be a lot more chill
than last dinner.

03:46.851 --> 03:48.395
Won't be any rumble?

03:48.436 --> 03:50.021
No, there won't be
any rumbles tonight.

03:50.063 --> 03:54.359
-No ultimatums?
-No ultimatums ever again.

03:54.401 --> 03:55.777
I'm always worried
I'm gonna get reprimanded.

04:03.785 --> 04:08.289
No, so, I've actually been
thinking about this for a while.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.708
I do wanna give you these.

04:09.749 --> 04:12.502
Yes! Stop!

04:12.544 --> 04:14.587
I don't want you to think
I'm just doing this now

04:14.629 --> 04:16.715
-because it's only me and you.
-Yeah.

04:16.756 --> 04:18.425
Like, I honestly think
you deserve this.

04:18.466 --> 04:20.343
Like, I never have
to ask you for anything.

04:20.385 --> 04:21.553
You're always just on it.

04:21.594 --> 04:23.513
You have worked your
----ing ass off,

04:23.555 --> 04:27.267
and without you,
I would be ----ed.

04:27.308 --> 04:28.560
Officially ----ed.

04:28.601 --> 04:30.478
-So...
-Yay!

04:31.688 --> 04:32.647
Oh.

04:32.689 --> 04:35.650
Thank you so much.

04:35.692 --> 04:37.610
Holy sh--.

04:37.652 --> 04:41.823
Dude, like, I see myself
like a junior stewardess.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.783
Oh, my God, stop it.

04:43.825 --> 04:46.327
It's nice to hear that
she actually notices,

04:46.369 --> 04:47.829
like, how hard I've been,
like, trying and stuff.

04:48.997 --> 04:50.749
Stop it.

04:50.790 --> 04:53.376
I've honestly learned so much,
and I'm so happy.

04:53.418 --> 04:54.461
Oh!

04:56.504 --> 04:59.049
Look!
I have a new stripe!

04:59.090 --> 05:00.925
What! Damn, girl!

05:00.967 --> 05:03.428
Congratulations, I salute you.

05:03.470 --> 05:05.430
You got way more stripes
than I'll ever have.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.933
I can take the carry-ons,
if you like.

05:08.975 --> 05:10.477
Yeah, thanks, Katie.

05:10.518 --> 05:12.395
Deck crew, we've got
luggage ready

05:12.437 --> 05:14.356
in the main deck lobby
whenever you guys are ready.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.982
Copy.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.567
It's been a busy morning.

05:17.609 --> 05:19.986
Oh, it's been a morning.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.404
You can take your mask off.

05:21.446 --> 05:22.739
It's been a rough
morning for Mzi.

05:22.781 --> 05:24.866
I think he's terrified
of me right now.

05:24.908 --> 05:28.661
Started off great,
I was all smiles and happy.

05:28.703 --> 05:30.372
It's just frustrating.

05:30.413 --> 05:32.665
Once you [bleep] one thing up
and your day starts off

05:32.707 --> 05:34.668
like that, it's just a bit
of a ripple effect.

05:34.709 --> 05:38.129
I know that I can do better,
and I should be doing better.

05:38.171 --> 05:40.924
How do I look, do I need to
go touch up or anything?

05:40.965 --> 05:42.092
You look beautiful, Malia.

05:42.133 --> 05:43.760
Oh, thank you, Mzi.

05:43.802 --> 05:45.470
Sure.

05:45.512 --> 05:47.931
Oh, suddenly I forgot
you dropped a heaving line.

05:49.557 --> 05:50.850
Katie, I'm gonna
leave this one for you.

05:50.892 --> 05:52.519
No!

05:52.560 --> 05:53.520
Yeah, yeah, I'm gonna
leave this one for you.

05:53.561 --> 05:54.938
-Actually?
-Yeah, yeah.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.523
Did you want me to
place your hat somewhere?

05:56.564 --> 05:57.941
-Sure, yeah.
-Promise I won't steal it.

05:57.982 --> 06:00.110
-Yeah, you can wear it.
-I really like it.

06:00.151 --> 06:01.528
Man, now I feel bad.

06:01.569 --> 06:02.529
I don't know if
I can accept this.

06:02.570 --> 06:03.530
No, yeah, I want you to have it.

06:03.571 --> 06:05.031
Thank you so much, Ben.

06:05.073 --> 06:06.991
It's a really nice gesture,
but it feels wrong

06:07.033 --> 06:09.536
because he was flirting, and
I don't wanna, like, egg it on.

06:09.577 --> 06:10.578
We're gonna fight over it now.

06:10.620 --> 06:12.539
Yeah, we are.

06:12.580 --> 06:14.416
It's a vibey hat,
I'm here for it.

06:16.501 --> 06:17.836
-Hey, Mzi?
-Yeah?

06:17.877 --> 06:19.504
Have you seen
my stripes recently?

06:19.546 --> 06:21.381
Where'd you get those?

06:21.423 --> 06:23.091
-Oh, second stew!
-She got promoted.

06:23.133 --> 06:25.427
Mine are still very green.

06:25.468 --> 06:26.594
Super happy for her.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.971
Where'd you get those?

06:32.142 --> 06:34.602
-Yay!
-Oh!

06:35.937 --> 06:37.564
Yeah, Courtney!

06:38.982 --> 06:40.525
Ready to go.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.444
All crew, all crew,
guest departure.

06:42.485 --> 06:43.903
On the dock in five minutes.

06:50.035 --> 06:51.161
<i>Mathew?</i>

06:51.202 --> 06:53.580
Mathew, Mathew,
come to the dock.

06:53.621 --> 06:55.498
<i>-On my way.</i>
-Thank you, Katie.

06:57.208 --> 06:58.626
Sorry, guys.

06:58.668 --> 07:00.045
Fancy seeing you here.

07:00.086 --> 07:02.589
I didn't realize
everybody was out already.

07:04.799 --> 07:06.593
Thanks, bro.

07:06.634 --> 07:07.927
Appreciate you.
Thanks.

07:07.969 --> 07:08.928
-Lovely to meet you, Ben.
-Yeah, likewise.

07:08.970 --> 07:10.680
Amazing!

07:10.722 --> 07:11.931
-Really special.
-Nicely done.

07:11.973 --> 07:13.933
Thank you very much,
appreciate it.

07:13.975 --> 07:15.143
Did you find it upstairs,
the hat?

07:15.185 --> 07:16.644
I haven't been up.

07:17.979 --> 07:20.774
My biggest thing with...
with all of you...

07:20.815 --> 07:22.984
well, Mat, your food's nuts.

07:23.026 --> 07:25.070
All of you, everything
that you guys offered,

07:25.111 --> 07:27.530
you did with a smile,
and it felt real genuine.

07:27.572 --> 07:28.948
We really
appreciate y'all's attitudes,

07:28.990 --> 07:30.700
so thank you very much.

07:30.742 --> 07:32.994
And we got a little
something for you.

07:33.036 --> 07:34.788
-Oh, thank you very much.
-Thank you guys.

07:34.829 --> 07:36.581
-Thank you so much.
-Thank you, nice to meet you.

07:36.623 --> 07:37.582
-Bye, we'll see you soon.
-See you soon.

07:37.624 --> 07:39.000
Nice work.

07:39.042 --> 07:40.960
Let's get out of our whites,
into our reds,

07:41.002 --> 07:42.462
and meet in the main salon
for our tip meeting.

07:42.504 --> 07:43.797
-Yeah.
-Woo!

07:45.173 --> 07:46.174
Yeah.

07:48.968 --> 07:50.220
One more.

07:50.261 --> 07:52.889
How do people get changed
so ----ing fast?

07:52.931 --> 07:54.015
-I don't know.
-Like...

07:54.057 --> 07:55.558
It's a talent.

07:57.852 --> 07:59.145
Thank you.

07:59.187 --> 08:01.606
Charter number six.

08:01.648 --> 08:04.651
Katie, I allowed you
the space not

08:04.693 --> 08:06.861
to bring on another stewardess.

08:06.903 --> 08:10.532
You showed me that
you could do this, so...

08:10.573 --> 08:13.827
-Thank you.
-Well done.

08:13.868 --> 08:16.663
I see the interior
is busting their asses.

08:16.705 --> 08:18.498
Like, they're working so hard.

08:18.540 --> 08:21.668
But last charter, I don't think
the work would have gotten done

08:21.710 --> 08:24.504
without the help of deck crew,
because it's just so much.

08:24.546 --> 08:27.882
Everyone's taking on
responsibility and clearly,

08:27.924 --> 08:31.136
deck crew is exhausted
and making stupid mistakes.

08:33.638 --> 08:35.932
Courtney, you're such
a positive energy,

08:35.974 --> 08:38.101
and you work really hard,
and I see that.

08:38.143 --> 08:39.769
Thanks.

08:39.811 --> 08:42.230
And Mathew, not one
client has ever complained,

08:42.272 --> 08:44.774
and I'm just, like, blown away.

08:44.816 --> 08:47.944
Deck crew, you guys...
you gotta work it out.

08:47.986 --> 08:51.156
You were challenged
with logistics,

08:51.197 --> 08:54.284
and you can be more focused.

08:54.325 --> 08:58.163
But you took it to the next
level for the beach picnic.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.206
-Thank you.
-Okay.

09:00.248 --> 09:04.336
So, $15,000...
$1,362 per person.

09:04.377 --> 09:06.046
Very grateful.

09:06.087 --> 09:08.590
So tonight, you know the wine
that we carry on board?

09:08.631 --> 09:10.050
You get to go to that winery.

09:10.091 --> 09:11.134
-Woo-hoo!
-Stop it!

09:11.176 --> 09:12.761
-Yes!
-Best day ever!

09:12.802 --> 09:14.262
Cheers, well done.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.308
Back on the train.

09:22.062 --> 09:23.980
Mzi, what's happening
to your hose?

09:24.022 --> 09:25.815
It was just spinning
out of control.

09:25.857 --> 09:28.234
They're having
a runaway water hose.

09:28.276 --> 09:30.570
So horny!

09:30.612 --> 09:31.946
Is that your runaway water hose?

09:33.782 --> 09:35.784
Come on, be professional.

09:35.825 --> 09:39.329
<i>Operation Water Hose, kinda</i>
<i>like Operation Line Handling.</i>

09:39.371 --> 09:42.582
The mistakes the guys are making
are kind of piggy-backing off

09:42.624 --> 09:44.376
of Captain Sandy's
disciplining me,

09:44.417 --> 09:46.753
so I'm a little
more on guard.

09:46.795 --> 09:49.714
I'm always trying to be
the best that I can be,

09:49.756 --> 09:52.175
and I always want
to impress Captain Sandy.

09:52.217 --> 09:54.260
I don't want her to think
that I'm a sh-- bosun.

09:54.302 --> 09:56.179
<i>Deck crew, let's meet</i>
<i>on the bow, please.</i>

09:58.348 --> 10:01.142
All right, guys, let's
have a quick deck meeting.

10:01.184 --> 10:02.644
I'm sure some of you noticed

10:02.686 --> 10:04.187
the tension on
deck this morning.

10:05.939 --> 10:06.898
-No?
-Yeah.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.274
Yes?

10:08.316 --> 10:10.110
Do we know why that is?

10:11.695 --> 10:13.613
Feedback...
this is an actual question.

10:13.655 --> 10:16.324
Do you guys understand why I
might have tension this morning?

10:20.453 --> 10:22.706
Coming up...

10:22.747 --> 10:24.624
Everyone's going through a
----ing rough time, and, like,

10:34.926 --> 10:36.386
I'm sure some of you noticed the
tension on deck this morning.

10:37.804 --> 10:41.141
Do we know why that is?

10:41.182 --> 10:43.143
Feedback...
this is an actual question.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.853
Do you guys understand
why I might be...

10:44.894 --> 10:46.271
have tension this morning?

10:49.357 --> 10:50.442
Okay.

10:52.360 --> 10:53.737
And the anchor ball.

10:53.778 --> 10:55.155
Please take
the anchor ball down.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.865
-Oh, sorry.
-For [bleep]'s sake.

10:56.906 --> 10:59.075
What do all these things
have in common?

11:00.243 --> 11:01.911
Exactly.

11:01.953 --> 11:03.329
We have crushed it,
everyone's been learning,

11:03.371 --> 11:05.999
and it really, really
gets under my skin

11:06.041 --> 11:08.084
when we start making
rookie, rookie mistakes.

11:08.126 --> 11:09.919
I mean, Mzi, you're green,

11:09.961 --> 11:11.463
but there's a point where
you have to give yourself

11:11.504 --> 11:13.173
a hard time about it
and say look,

11:13.214 --> 11:15.008
I shouldn't be making
these mistakes anymore.

11:15.050 --> 11:16.384
And that's how you
stop being green.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.053
-Yeah.
-It's charter six.

11:18.094 --> 11:20.764
You should always know
what to do next.

11:20.805 --> 11:22.432
Dave, I know you
weren't up for it.

11:22.474 --> 11:25.268
I walked in at the perfect time
to see you chatting to Mathew.

11:25.310 --> 11:28.188
But you see me hustling,
I expect to see you hustling.

11:28.229 --> 11:30.065
You have four minutes.

11:30.106 --> 11:32.359
-How's it going?
-Yeah, it's gonna be a new...

11:32.400 --> 11:34.736
David, get out
on deck, please, now.

11:34.778 --> 11:36.279
Heaving lines, set up.

11:36.321 --> 11:38.406
You're usually the guy
I can count on

11:38.448 --> 11:40.367
to set a good example
for everyone.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.160
You're either meeting
that benchmark, or you're not.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.245
Mm.

11:44.287 --> 11:48.041
I will work through anything
so as not to let my team down.

11:48.083 --> 11:51.753
But I was asked to take
a step back because of my leg.

11:51.795 --> 11:52.879
I did.

11:56.299 --> 11:58.301
When you step off this boat
and you start looking

11:58.343 --> 12:00.011
for your next job,

12:00.053 --> 12:02.305
you can expect someone
to not be as nice about it.

12:03.306 --> 12:05.100
You can expect that.

12:05.141 --> 12:08.853
So, what I want is for our next
charter to absolutely nail it,

12:08.895 --> 12:11.439
because I know you're better,
and I wanna look it, okay?

12:11.481 --> 12:13.983
On that note,
let's get some trash off.

12:14.025 --> 12:15.485
Good chat.

12:24.077 --> 12:25.829
You okay?

12:25.870 --> 12:27.372
I'll be back next charter.

12:28.915 --> 12:30.417
What are you gonna
drink tonight?

12:32.293 --> 12:33.503
Yeah, but what piss
are you gonna suck?

12:33.545 --> 12:35.547
-Probably pink.
-No!

12:35.588 --> 12:38.091
Why am I... why do...
why am I not allowed rosé?

12:38.133 --> 12:40.010
It's when we see
Mr. Extra Nasty.

12:40.051 --> 12:41.177
No, no, no, I'm gonna be...

12:41.219 --> 12:42.387
like, no matter
how much I drink,

12:42.429 --> 12:43.471
I'll be a good boy tonight.

12:43.513 --> 12:45.098
I don't have anyone to sass.

12:45.140 --> 12:47.225
Talk to me, bro.
What's up?

12:47.267 --> 12:48.560
What happened this morning?

12:48.601 --> 12:50.145
I didn't put
the paddleboards out.

12:50.186 --> 12:51.563
Oh, right.

12:51.604 --> 12:53.523
Sandy just asked why
they weren't there,

12:53.565 --> 12:55.442
and then for the heaving lines,

12:55.483 --> 12:56.526
I think Malia was getting
a bit tense.

12:56.568 --> 12:58.236
Mm-hmm.

12:58.278 --> 12:59.904
